8. DATA MANAGEMENT
================================================================================

8.1 Data Collection
• Platform: Google Forms (online survey)
• Period: 10 March – 15 April 2026
• De-identification: All personal identifiers removed; synthetic participant 
  IDs assigned (P001–P303)

8.2 Data Storage
• Raw data: Encrypted local storage, access restricted to research team
• De-identified dataset: CSV format, available via GitHub and Zenodo
• Analysis code: Python scripts, MIT License, version-controlled

8.3 Documentation Record
• Supplementary Document S1: Transparent reporting record prepared post-analysis
• Includes: Analysis decisions, sensitivity results, deviation log

Data collection coincided with World Intellectual Property Day 2026 awareness activities conducted at Manara University. These activities were independent of the study design, were not implemented as an intervention, and were not evaluated analytically.

The STROBE checklist and reproducibility materials are publicly available through the GitHub repository and permanently archived on Zenodo: https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20716883. 

================================================================================
9. LIMITATIONS AND CONSTRAINTS
================================================================================

9.1 Design Limitations
• Cross-sectional design precludes causal inference
• Convenience sampling limits generalizability
• Self-reported data introduces potential common-method variance

9.2 Measurement Limitations
• Formative composite indicators have low internal consistency by conventional 
  psychometric standards (range 0.481–0.524)
• These coefficients reflect intentional heterogeneity, not construct invalidity
• Traditional reliability metrics are not appropriate validity criteria

9.3 Explanatory Limitations
• Models explain limited variance (R² ≤ 0.20)
• Substantial unobserved structural factors likely shape innovation practice
• Any interpretation involving mechanisms or system-level causation is 
  provisional

